Everyone I know in the political world was up late (very late) last night a=
nd out of bed early (very early) this morning, scrolling their social media=
 feeds frantically and refreshing their browsers obsessively to keep abreas=
t of any and all fresh, credible information related to the first set of qu=
estions. And, in their collective and respective states of shock, Democrats=
 and Republicans of goodwill alike, were talking with their colleagues, pee=
rs, and bosses about what could be done=E2=80=94what they could do=E2=80=94=
cool things off and avoid the very real possibility that the assassination =
attempt could set off any number of escalatory chain reactions that would d=
rive us all further into the darkness.

One result of those conversations was evident this morning inside the Trump=
 campaign. After tweeting last night, =E2=80=9CWell of course they tried to=
 keep
him off the ballot, they tried to put him in jail and now you see this,=E2=
=80=9D LaCivita took that post down, and then together with Wiles issued a =
memo to their staff saying they would, =E2=80=9Cnot tolerate dangerous rhet=
oric on social media.=E2=80=9D Another result was President Biden=E2=80=99s=
 address from the Oval Office tonight, in which he urged America to =E2=80=
=9Clower the temperature=E2=80=9D on our political rhetoric, and noted, =E2=
=80=9CWe don=E2=80=99t yet have any information about the motive of the sho=
oter. We know who he is. I urge everyone, everyone: Please don=E2=80=99t ma=
ke assumptions about his motives or his affiliations. Let the FBI do their =
job.=E2=80=9D

Biden=E2=80=99s remarks about the shooter=E2=80=99s motives were a veiled r=
ebuke to a wide array of Republicans who, in the wake of the shooting, took=
 to social media to spout precisely the kind of baseless and incendiary bul=
lshit that has made our current circumstances so fucking rotten, and so dan=
gerous. South Carolina Senator Tim Scott blamed ( https://x.com/votetimscot=
t/status/1812290893312901259?utm_campaign=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SU=
BSCRIBERS+%287%2F14%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBS=
CRIBERS+%286%2F30%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.i=
o&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) the =E2=80=9Cradical Left and corporate m=
edia=E2=80=9D for what happened in Butler. Ohio senator and apparent frontr=
unner in the Trump veepstakes J.D. Vance claimed=20
( https://x.com/JDVance1/status/1812280973628965109?utm_campaign=3DThe+Best=
+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%287%2F14%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Best+%=
26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%286%2F30%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&=
utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) that =E2=80=9Cthe =
central premise of the Biden campaign =E2=80=A6 that Trump is an authoritar=
ian fascist who must be stopped at all costs =E2=80=A6 led directly=E2=80=
=9D to the shooting.

Along with many others on the right, Georgia Congressman Mike Collins cited=
 a reported comment of Biden=E2=80=99s on a recent call with donors=E2=80=
=94=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s time to put Trump in
the bull=E2=80=99s-eye=E2=80=9D=E2=80=94and then put a none too fine point =
on the matter: =E2=80=9CBiden sent the orders,=E2=80=9D Collins tweeted ( h=
ttps://x.com/MikeCollinsGA/status/1812257581655531669?utm_campaign=3DThe+Be=
st+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%287%2F14%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Best=
+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%286%2F30%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_actio=
n&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ). Conservative pu=
ndit Erick Erickson proudly pointed out that he=E2=80=99s said for months (=
 https://ewerickson.substack.com/p/msnbc-wants-trump-assassinated?utm_campa=
ign=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%287%2F14%2F24%29&utm_conten=
t=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%286%2F30%2F24%29&utm_medium=
=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) th=
at =E2=80=9CMSNBC wants Trump assassinated=E2=80=9D and then inveighed agai=
nst The New Republic for its June cover=20
( https://x.com/FischerKing64/status/1812261393124696270?utm_campaign=3DThe=
+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%287%2F14%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+B=
est+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%286%2F30%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_ac=
tion&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ), which portra=
ys Trump as Hitler.

I don=E2=80=99t have the energy or inclination to devote the time for an ep=
ic rant laying out the extent and degree of mendacity, perniciousness, and =
corrosive bad faith that these reactions embody and entail. But I will simp=
ly note that not one of these, or the other like minded shit-posters on thi=
s topic, has seen fit to acknowledge one of the few hard facts about Thomas=
 Crooks, the Bethel Park, Pennsylvania, 20-year-old identified by law enfor=
cement as Trump=E2=80=99s wannabe killer: He was a registered Republican. T=
his may or may not end up being meaningful in any way=E2=80=94we have no id=
ea at this point. Which is precisely the goddamn point.

