t-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">much-discussed magnum opus</a></u> in <i>The A=
tlantic</i> on the <b>Trump</b> campaign. When it comes to the G.O.P. and t=
he right more broadly, there=E2=80=99s no long-form journalist in the busin=
ess better than Alberta, whose work is, as a rule, deeply reported, beautif=
ully written,
and perfectly timed. And this new piece is no exception. It features the Tr=
ump campaign=E2=80=99s co-managers, <b>Chris LaCivita</b> and <b>Susie Wile=
s</b>, boasting about the historic drubbing they believe they have in store=
